animal.description:
Winona mom (Willa) came to our shelter VERY pregnant and delivered six puppies just days after arriving to her foster home.  The babies struggled a lot in their first three months of life- horrible coccidia, major worm infestations, and a case of parvo that nearly took their lives.  Thanks to an amazing team of volunteers who worked around the clock (and a team of veterinary professionals too), all six puppies (and mom) survived. 

Winona  is a pretty girl looking for a forever family. She is 15 weeks old and weighs 20+ pounds.  She is expected to be about 70-80 lbs at adult weight. Her mom is a Rottie/Hound Mix (see photo- Willa) and we don't know a thing about dad.  Based on her size and shape of her head, we're guessing he was a Mastiff or Great Dane mix.

Winona is spayed; vaccinated for rabies, distemper, and bordetella; and microchipped with a lifetime registration. She is current on flea/tick and prevention too.

Interested in meeting Winona? Please visit our website www.HalfwayHomeRescue.org and complete an adoption application. Adoption donation $550.

We anticipate a LOT of applications for these puppies.  At this time, we are ONLY accepting applications from CT residents.  Applicants must own their homes and be able to provide proof of ownership.  Applications that do not meet the criteria, will not be considered.

animal.description:
*We are not hosting adoption events at Petco for the public at this time*
We are currently very busy and have over 100 applications to review and on file. Thank you for your patience! We are working to find everyone a companion. 

Dino is an adorable 9week old lab mix. 

If you are interested in adopting the first step is to fill out an adoption application on our website aaanimalrescue.org. We are currently very busy! Please reach out to allaboardanimalrescue@gmail.com if you have an approved application on file! Please fill out an adoption application on our website if you are ready to adopt! 

Thank you for your patience and understanding during this difficult time! We are on a mission to find everyone companions, we will continue to rescue dogs weekly! We update our page every Monday evening. We are not currently hosting any Petco adoption events for the public. We will be hosting meet/greet adoption appointments!


Breed and size disclosure: As a rescue all of our dogs come to us from high-kill shelters or other rescues, so we do not get a lot of background or information on these dogs. We occasionally receive the mother with the puppies, but in most cases both parents are unknown. Because of this we do not know the full breeding of the dogs. We are required to list the dogs based on the breeds provided to us on their records, but they are all mixed breeds as far as we know, and we cannot guarantee the actual breeds of any of these dogs. Since the full breeding of the dogs is unknown we can also only give you an educated guess on the full-grown size of the dogs. All of the current information we have on the dogs is listed in their bio above. More information may be available at our adoption event, since a lot of the fosters turn in report cards on how the dog has done in their care when they drop them off. 

Adoption Process: If you are interested in adopting from us, the first step of our adoption process is to fill out an application online at http://aaanimalrescue.org/adoption_app.html. It takes us 24-48 hours to process your application and get back to you, via email. Applications turned in Friday afternoon or Saturday morning will not be processed since we are preparing for or at our adoption event. We do have applications on site at our events, but are not always able to approve them at that time and many of the dogs will already have holds on them, so we suggest you fill out an application prior to attending an adoption event. We can place a hold on one dog per approved applicant after a deposit fee has been received, please do not ask to hold a dog if you have not turned in an application and been approved, for the first hour of our adoption event, so that they can get the first chance to meet and hopefully adopt that dog. After the first hour of the event all dogs are available on a first come, first serve basis. If you already have an approved application on file, there will just be more paperwork and the adoption fee at the event, but you will be able to take home the dog/puppy that day. Since we are foster based and do not have a location, our dogs are only available to meet at our events, unless otherwise noted.

animal.description:
Meet Broc, a 1yo boy who will be looking for his forever family soon!

Broc loves to be with his people and is good with all dogs. He came into rescue very emaciated and we are working closely with our vet to determine any underlying condition as the cause for this. Broc is curious about cats and currently working on house training. He will be fully vetted, vaccinated and microchipped prior to adoption.

We will require Broc to be in basic obedience training within 30 days of adoption. Basic obedience training is a great opportunity for Broc to bond with his new family, learn new commands and reinforce good manners.  

For more information about our adoption process and an application please visit www.whitekissesgreatdanerescue.com/adopt

animal.description:
Reign - Female
MinPin/Chihuahua Mix (Breed is best guess only)
DOB 11/1/2020
Current Weight 5 pounds

NO CHILDREN UNDER THE AGE OF 10
Meet Reign. Coming in second smallest of the 3, she and her siblings were surrendered to a high kill animal control. It was a pretty scary place but they all came to Illinois in hopes of finding their forever homes. Though small she is an energetic puppy with lots of love to give. She loves to be held, playing with her siblings, (both canine and human) and her toys. She is learning all the basic puppy manners which consist of crate training, potty training. Due to her size we are asking no small children and she cannot be left home alone more then a few hours to continue her training and socialization. Are you Reign’s forever home?. If interested please fill out an application on our website www.foreverhomedogrescueil.org


WE DO NOT DO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS
Thank you for considering the adoption of one of our rescue dogs.  We are committed to finding our rescues the perfect home. Together we can make a difference in the life of a dog.
 
The adoption process should be a fun and exciting time for families and dogs. Our goal is to place our babies in forever homes.  The potential adopter needs to be dedicated to their care and training for life. 
Understand that sharing your life with a dog can be a commitment of 15+ years. This would include feeding, exercise, training, vetting, and providing a loving home. Ask yourself, "Am I ready for this type of commitment?"  If you are ready, we are here to help.  We do have some requirements to help us find the perfect placement of our babies. 

WE ARE A FOSTER BASED RESCUE ONLY. WE DO NOT HAVE A PHYSICAL BUILDING
1.  Apply online at https://www.foreverhomedogrescueil.org
We must have an application, conduct a phone interview, and meet your entire family (including other dogs) to approve an adoption. Only a final approval for adoption can take place after a successful meet and greet. This is done by appointments only. We will not proceed with the adoption if everyone has not met the dog.  This will allow others the opportunity to adopt the dog.
2.  Adopters MUST be 21 years old.
Information on all adults/members living in the home is required
We REQUIRE you to provide proof and vet reference that all current and past pets have been kept up to date on all routine medical.
3.  Illinois law requires that all of our dogs and puppies be spayed/neutered within 30 days of adoption. In order to fully comply with this regulation and reduce the number of homeless dogs and puppies, 
4.  If you do not own your home, you must provide landlord contact information on the application and a copy of your lease that outlines the rules for dog ownership in your residence.  
Large breed dogs will not be adopted into apartment settings or where there are breed/ size restrictions.
Puppies have special needs and require a home where someone is available to care for, socialize, and give basic training.  If you are gone for more than a couple hours at a time, please consider adopting a teen or older dog.
5.  Adoption fees are $350. We accept checks or cash. (Prices are subject to change without notice).
6.  All dogs and puppies adopted through Forever Home are fully vetted with age appropriate vaccines. Keep in mind once you take possession of your newly adopted dog, any and all future medical costs or care is YOUR responsibility.
7. First time puppy/dog adopters will be required to sign up for and pay in advance a basic training class. A deposit of an extra 50.00 will be required until a class has been completed, it will then be returned. 
8. WE DO NOT DO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS 
 
Medical included is as follows:
Spay/Neuter (age appropriate) *Forever Home uses Fox Valley Animal Welfare League in Aurora, IL
Age appropriate core vaccines
Fecal testing and deworming
Flea and tick preventative
Free 1st Vet visit at one of our participating vets
Microchipping
 
Forever Home Dog Rescue reserves the right to deny any applicant.

animal.description:
Sadie is ready for her FOREVER HOME!!
She’s days away from 1 year old, DOB 1/31/20. She currently weighs in an estimated 70 lbs, but I expect she’ll fill out and possibly grow a little more. Her primary breed is Great Pyrenees; possibly with Golden Retriever. She is spayed.

Sadie is one the sweetest, cuddliest dogs I’ve ever been around. If a potential owner is looking for a giant blonde fluffy shadow, this is the dog for them. Potential owners must be aware that she’s a hand nudger! If you have a empty or available hand, she will immediately be shoving her nose into it searching for pets! Like most giant breeds, she plays hard and runs in spurts but will happily sleep and laze around the house for hours on end. Sadie loves being around her people and pack, so she doesn’t necessarily like her kennel. She’s learning and with time and patience has started to adjust wonderfully. She’s pretty sedate for a dog so young. One of her favorite things is to take the squeaky ball out of the toy and then just play with the toy. Overall, she’s a very gentle, sweet, loving girl; who will thrive with the right family. Just be prepared for all her hair!!

Sadie has not been around children but we would assume so she would be good; she’s been wonderful around all adult people she’s met. She gets along with other dogs; not sure about cats since she’s never met one. She DOES NOT get along with chickens (or any birds really). 

She is house trained and will “alert” at the door when she needs to go outside. While she has had a few accidents in a kennel over the past 2 weeks, mostly she is kennel trained. Her main issue is learning to self sooth and relax in her kennel. She does know simple commands of sit, down, stay, and come but she is still a puppy and gets herself distracted. She has been caught counter-surfing a handle of times, but responds to a firm No (I think she knows she’s not supposed to). She’s up to date on shots and heart worm negative but will need her next pill shortly. As an extra note, she’s been eating Royal Canin Giant Breed adult formula.

This dog is a Benefactor Dog. His/her increased adoption fee will allow them to act as a benefactor to other dogs in our care that require special medical care and a better chance at adoption.

If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (that application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

 The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information.

2021 Adoption Fee Scale:
Benefactor Puppies under 12 months - $500
Benefactor Dogs over 12 months - $400


*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

animal.description:
*PLEASE NOTE: ADOPTERS INTERESTED IN MRS. JONES MUST HAVE ANOTHER DOG*

Mrs. Jones is a 2.5 year old spayed female Carolina Dog mix who weighs about 50 lbs. Mrs. Jones was rescued from an overcrowded shelter after being found as a stray. To say the shelter was a scary place for this girl is an understatement. All she wanted to do is run away. We cannot wait until she feels safe enough and realizes she doesn't have to flee. Once she gets to know you, Mrs. Jones is very sweet and gentle. She seems to prefer women over men, and doesn't feel comfortable with kids. She absolutely loves other dogs, and would love a confident canine sibling to help show her what a dog's life should be. She will need a patient family willing to give her time to settle in and realize she is out of harms way. A quieter home would be best for her as she is easily scared of loud noises. Mrs. Jones is so deserving of a dedicated forever family to call her very own. Please help us find Mrs. Jones the forever home she's been searching for!

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/
We are a foster based organization, so we do not have a facility to visit. Please read our FAQs to learn more: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/faq
Follow us on Facebook for foster updates and a full list of our adoptable pets: https://www.facebook.com/all4pawsrescue/

animal.description:
Odie is a 1 yr old male chihuahua terrier mix that weighs 12 lbs.  He is very sweet, friendly, loves to snuggle and be by your side.  He loves to play with toys and will bring them back to you. He will destroy the toys to get to the squeaker, but is not destructive in the house.  

He’s not a barker and we are working on his house training.  He was found running the streets of Tijuana with 2 other dogs. Unfortunately while he was living on the streets he was hit by a car and one of his legs was broken.  It is completely healed and he just needs more exercise to continue to strengthen his leg. He walks on it but sometimes he doesn’t. 

Odie is fine around other dogs but has a very dominant personality so we prefer he be the only dog in the household.  He does not like to share his attention and may snap at another dog. He’s great around cats, the foster has one and says he ignores the cat. He is ready to find his forever home. 

Odie is neutered, up-to-date on vaccines and microchipped.  If you are interested in him, please complete the on-line application that can be found on our website: www.adoptmerescue.org or contact us for more information.

Local area adoption only.

Gunner (responds to Axl) is approximately 2.5 years old, 10 lbs. He has so much personality and and a very impressive vertical leap for such a tiny guy!! He absolutely loves snuggling and loving on his humans, as well as barking at kids outside. He has a major little man complex and always wants to be the alpha dog. He does not get along well with other dominant dogs therefore he should probably be the only dog in the home. He cries a bit when his humans leave the house which may not be ideal for apartments or condos with shared walls. This guy really knows how to lay the cuteness on thick, and will make a great companion for some lucky person.... is it you?!

animal.description:
***Thank you for your interest in Magnificent Mutts and Meows. We hope everyone is saying safe during this challenging time. Due to the current regulations set forth by Governor Pritzker on group gatherings we will not be having adoption events until further notice. As an all foster based rescue this means that all meets will be by appointment only. Your whole family must be available to attend the meet as there will be no second meets scheduled to help limit contact between our team and the public. To help streamline the process please make sure your current pets are up to date, you have landlord/HOA approval, and that you are prepared to take the dog home with you immediately before submitting an application. Thank you & Please stay safe!***

These cuties came into rescue less than a week old. Network to us from a rescue partner in the south they are now approximately 8 weeks old and ready to find their forever homes!

Breed and size once full grown is not a guarantee as they came into rescue with only mom (Wiggles pictured) and dad is unknown.

If you are interested in adoption, please complete the Application to Adopt which you can find on our website (
www.magnificentmutts.org
) No phone calls please. Emails only.

Adoption Donation $300 (cash only)

Please visit www.magnificentmutts.org for the online dog or cat application.

Adoption Fees*

Adult cats starting at $125, Kittens starting at $165.
Dogs/Puppies starting at $225 minimum
Prices subject to change, please contact for specific adoption donations.

animal.description:
Brandy 
Male
Poodle Mix
10 lbs 
8 years 

My name is Brandy. My mom died and her family couldn’t keep me and four of her dogs, so I’m grateful New Hope took us so we didn’t have to go to the shelter.

My foster describes me as a “stereotypical miniature poodle” in that I’m all about my humans and that’s about it! I’m an amazing lapdog and white I get along peacefully with other dogs, I’m probably not going to be a playmate for other pups in your house. I like to have the human attention on me!

I can be somewhat vocal (I whine) when I want attention and foster dad is working on my potty training and says I’m making huge progress.  Foster dad crates me when he leaves the house and at night.  I’m not a huge fan of the crate since I want to be close to you but I tolerate it.   

I don’t seem top lay with toys and I’m medium energy and highly food and treat motivated.   My my leash training is in progress and I’m currently enjoying short walks and stick close to my foster dad when I’m in the yard.  

If you are excited about meeting me, please fill out an adoption application right away as it's the first step! 

https://nhanimalrescue.org/adoption-information/

animal.description:
Katie Sparkles is a 46 pound, beautiful 9 month old yellow lab mix.  She is sweet and loving.   She enjoys playing chase in the yard and chasing squirrels.   She LOVES kids.   She acts shy at first, but warms up quickly.   She will make the perfect family dog and deserves her very own furever family.    

All our adoption fees include spay/neuter, micro-chip, up-to-date vaccinations, including rabies thru date of adoption. This pup tested heartworm negative, and is on regular monthly heartworm prevention & on flea/tick prevention. 

In order to be considered for one of our beautiful pups, please go to our website and complete and application: https://www.mustluvdogs.org/adoptable-pets.
Please note that we are a DUE DILIGENCE adoption organization. Part of our approval process requires, among other things:
* Experienced pet home with verifiable vet references/history preferred, but we realize that everyone has to start somewhere, so all applications will be considered.
*The majority, but not all, of our pets require a fenced yard or secure enclosure.  In the case of apartments, we require Landlord approval and designated dog area in complex.
*Verifiable good veterinary history INCLUDING regular vaccination/visits and good Heartworm Prevention history is a MUST!
*Adopter must be able to have time to spend with the pup and be able to provide the pup a safe environment to live.
*ALL our dogs are expected to be primarily INSIDE dogs.  They MUST sleep inside the home.  We truly understand that some folks have working dogs (i.e. farmers, ranchers,etc); however, the majority of our dogs have had a rough life prior to coming to us & we want to make sure that they are showered with LUV & maybe even a bit spoiled for the rest of their lives. 

Other facts are also considered, including whether children or other pets are a good fit with the dog. 

Must Luv Dogs reserves the right to deny any applications that we don't think are a good fit with the pup. Our first & foremost concern is the dog's best interest. It is our MISSION to place them in a home that is a great fit for their needs for a lifetime of luv & being part of a family.
*We will consider adoptions in any area; however, will do not ship or transport puppies under the age of 12 mos. We will ONLY transport an adult dog on a transport approved by MLD, at adopter's expense.
* In order to be affordable and afford every family an opportunity to have a pup of their own, we keep our Adoption Fees low; however, please keep in mind that the fees we charge do not cover all costs for the pup.  Any additional donations are greatly appreciated!

Please note that all of our pets are in private foster homes. In order to reduce any stress or confusion for our pups, we require a completed, approved application BEFORE setting up a meet & greet for any of our pups.  Alternatively, you are always welcome to come meet any of our pups at one of our regular Adoption Events.   Our events are always posted on PetFinder OR on our Facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/mustLUVdogs.org.

Finally, THANK YOU for considering Must Luv Dogs for your next pet. 

*Most dogs require a fenced area in yard. 
*Apartments okay IF nearby dog park or walking trails (with landlord appoval).
*ALL dogs must be INSIDE dogs and treated a part of family. 
*We are a DUE DILIGENCE Adoption Rescue.  
*Must have good Vet history & Heartworm prevention is a MUST!
*ALL dogs are fully vetted, spay/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption.

FYI:   Even though this pup tested heartworm negative, we provide the following procedural information for your information:  Any of our pups who test HW+ are treated with the *slow kill method of treatment.   The *slow-kill method, simply stated, is a 30 day regiment of  doxycycline followed by a monthly dose of Advantage Multi for 12 months, then retesting.   Most dogs test negative after one year of following this treatment; however, we always recommend that potential adopters consult & follow the advice of their family veterinarian upon adopting any of our hw+ pups.   Although the fast-kill method is still considered the "gold-standard" by the AVA, and may be preferred by some vets; the slow-kill method has proven to be effective in our rescue. The main reason we utilize this method is due to our limited financial constraints and the high number of our rescue pups that are infected.   In the cases of severe infection and if the pup is highly symptomatic, we sometimes use the fast-kill approach instead.   Again, we recommend for you to consult with your veterinarian after the adoption is complete and follow their recommendations.

Very loving & sweet but shyHere is Zima!

She came to us from a local county pound with her litter of 5 pups. They are now old enough to be weaned so now we can focus on finding her the home she deserves! We estimate her to be around 2-3 yrs old and is currently 44#.

She is a HUGE sweetheart, very calm but still very shy. She will really benefit from an owner that will help her through exposure to different things and socialization in public to help build her confidence. She is very weary of new people, but if you go slowly she takes no time at all to warm up and wants all the love that you can give.

We are working on crate training and house breaking, and she's doing very well! She has ignored the cat and other dogs in the house.

Young children will not be a good fit for her at this time as she is still very skittish and loud, fast movements will most likely frighten her.

Do you have the patience and kindness to help this girl blossom?

She will be up to date on all vaccinations, microchipped and spayed at the time of her adoption (her spay will be in a couple weeks as she just weaned her puppies). animal.description:
Meet Macaroni!  He is a young male rat terrier mix that is looking for a forever home.  He loves to be picked up and held and will give you a lot of kisses when he gets to know you.  He has tons of energy and loves to play.  His favorite toys are ones that make noises because he talks back to them!  

Macaroni needs an experienced dog owner that will help work with him on his training. He is still working on his potty-training.  He has a big personality and can occasionally be nippy, so a home without small children would be best.  He has a silly stubborn side to him and doesn't always liked to be scolded, so he will need someone who is comfortable working with him.  He is ready to love and bond with the kind person who will be patient with him and train him to be the best he can be.  

The NAWS Dog Adoption Program operates as a rescue versus a shelter.  We believe in matching the right dog with the appropriate family based on each specific dog or family's needs.  To achieve this, we believe in spending the appropriate amount of time with each family to allow for enough interaction time with potential adopters.  This cannot be achieved if people stop by unexpectedly to meet our dogs.  Please e-mail Stacy at stacy@nawsus.org to setup a day or time to meet with one of our adoption counselors and our potential adoptees.  Thank you!

For my Petfinder.com friends, please contact the Shelter at (248) 858-1070 for more information. My ID number is 337312

Meet Akasha! Gorgeous Akasha is looking to find, just the right person to move in with! After two years in her home, Akasha had to come to the Shelter. Seems she has not much training, and her former people chose not to peruse that avenue! Akasha is a sweet, young, girl who is bursting with potential. She is a smart lady who knows basic commands, and is quite eager to learn. Akasha enjoys being brushed, really likes to play and especially is fond of going for walks. This deserving girl, is patiently waiting for a fantastic, energetic new owner, to swoop her up! Akasha will thrive in a home with older children.

The above behaviors and personality traits have been observed while at the Shelter. If this animal was relinquished, information is gathered from the owner regarding behavior. Our wonderful volunteers spend time with these animals and give input on behaviors and traits. However, this description may not be all inclusive to how this animal will act in a loving forever home. Introduction to established family pets should be slow and monitored always. The same goes for children and other family members. Adopting a pet is a big decision and should be thoughtful. We suggest researching different breeds to match traits and personalities to your lifestyle. When adopting a pet, please know that this pet will be with you for their lifetime; patience and consistency will make for a successful adoption.

Confident, courageous and smart are just some of the adjectives to describe the Shepherd. There is a reason that police departments use these beautiful dogs to work alongside of policemen and policewomen; loyalty, the ability to learn commands and willingness to put their lives on the line in defense of their family. They were originally bred to herd livestock; so, this breed will need exercise and not just physical but mental as well.

animal.description:
-Ben is a 9 year old Pitty Mix. He is current on his vaccines, neutered, house trained, crate trained, microchipped, and adorable.
     -He is extremely friendly to any human he has ever met including kids and toddlers. Sadly, he is not good with other animals because of abuse before I got him. However, I have found it very easy to keep him away from other dogs on walks. Ben enjoys playing fetch and hardcore tug of war. As he is older though, it seems that his favorite activity is to curl up next to me while I am working. The best way to describe Ben is "attached at the hip"; he is just happiest when he is with humans and interacting. 
     -In order to calm some of his anxiety, Ben is on prozac which costs approx $8/month and can be picked up at any pharmacy. His prescription is half used and will be good for another 3 months before his vet can issue a new one. 
     -Ben is highly trained and knows a wide variety of commands. Although he is house trained, I would recommend crating him if you leave the house as he is most distraught when alone and tends to have a hard time not peeing on something. However, he is fine unattended as long as he knows you are in the house with him.
     -I am rehoming Ben because I am getting married and my fiance and I aren't able to afford a house where our pets can be separated safely and her cat is much older than Ben and not likely to survive the trauma of being rehomed. 

Ben is a courtesy post and not a Hello Pitty Rescue. Please reach out directly to 
Kyle Scribner at kylescribbles@gmail.com

animal.description:
Boots is a beautiful 1 year old Shepard Mix. She adores her foster mom and playing with her foster fur brother. Boots loves being pet, affection, and to have her ears scratched. She isn't fond of her crate, but will go in without too much fuss if necessary. She barks for a few minutes when she first goes in her crate, but otherwise she is an extremely quiet dog. She doesn't bark when the door bell rings or when she hears the neighbor dogs bark. Boots shows no interest in chewing or destruction and will mostly likely be able to be trusted crate free in the home after she settles in. She is potty trained and has no accidents in her foster home. She will quickly pick up which door to stand by to alert you she needs to go out. She is a gentle giant who thinks she is a small lap dog and is happy to just be around her people on the couch watching a movie or as a work from home assistant in your home office. She is eager to please, intelligent, loyal, and loves treats so training her should be a breeze. She's an easy going dog who would love the opportunity to go to doggy school for a beginner obedience class to learn some basics (stay, leave it, go to a bed) and help her build confidence. She has never had to opportunity to learn leash manners but loves walks and has responded well to her first leash training sessions with her foster mom. Her new family should continue basic leash training with her. She doesn't show any interest in cats. Because of her size and her slight shyness with sudden movement she would do best in a home with children 10+. Boots is a social dog and will do best with another dog in the home if she has to be away from you most of the day. She would love a family who will take her on walks, jogs, or hikes. She loves to run around the backyard, but after her energy is out she is a zen lapdog. She enjoys having a fenced yard to run around, but will do okay without one if she gets walks each day. Boots is the type of dog you can take anywhere...the beach, dog park, camping...she's up for anything as long as she can be with her family. She's a great car passenger, she sits in the backseat and enjoys the ride. What she wants most in the world is to be a loyal companion in a family.

Boots was rescued from Oklahoma and is a 1 yr female Shepherd mix weighing approx. 50 lbs. Boots is dog and cat friendly.

If you would like to meet Boots please complete an online application that can be found at: http://hopeanimalrescueofiowa.org/forms/196/dog-application

Adoption fee is $250 which includes spay/neuter, age-appropriate vaccines/tests, and microchip.

I am looking for a lap to call my own, a wardrobe of XS sweaters and dresses, and maybe a doggy purse so I can go everywhere with you! My owner died and I came to rescue without a name. animal.description:
This dog is in Tennessee. Adoption Donation $200 if picked up in TN, $250 plus transport fee for out of state adoptions.

Awesome Axel is ready to say hello! He is a 16-month-old, 77 pound goofball of a puppy with energy to spare. If you love the protective nature of a German Shepherd, you'll appreciate Axel. He has a big bark and is an excellent watchdog - he will let you know with anything is out of the ordinary on your property. He's looking for someone who will appreciate him just as is he, but he is definitely receptive to training and loves food and play as rewards. The best environment for Axel would be a calm, adult-only home with a securely fenced yard and another similar size and energy-level dog friend. He would also be fine by himself, as long as he got plenty of attention from his family. Axel is very energetic, he loves to run zoomies around the house and yard and loves toys, chew bones, chasing squirrels and playing fetch. He is generally friendly but can be wary of strangers especially behind a fence or barrier. Axel is not aggressive to cats but definitely thinks they are fun to play chase if they run. Axel is house trained and crate trained. He thrives with a routine and lots of exercise. He has recovered from a skin condition (but may have some ongoing allergies) and knee surgery and is now healthy and ready for a family of his own. If you think this big silly boy would be a match for your family, please apply today.

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: http://aarf-tn.com/adopt/adoption-apps/

If you have questions that are not covered in the profile, visit the Pet Inquiry Form: http://aarf-tn.com/contact/pet-inquiry-form/.

THIS PET IS FOSTERED IN TENNESSEE! We do list and adopt our pets nationwide. Typical transport cost to the Northeast is $160. Due to interstate adoption regulations, we are not able to adopt to RI and MA state residents.

A.A.R.F. (All About Rescue and Fixin' Inc.) http://aarf-tn.com/ is a non-profit, 501(c)(3) no kill animal rescue organization located in the Upper Cumberland area of Tennessee. A.A.R.F. is comprised of unpaid volunteers and survives only on public donations. Thank you for thinking adoption first!

Prior to adoption, all canines and felines are spayed or neutered, have received their age appropriate vaccinations, have been de-wormed for common parasites, and have received treatment for prevention of fleas and ticks. All canines over the age of 6 months have been tested for heartworm. All canines are put on heartworm prevention as soon as possible - this means dogs as soon as they are tested negative. Puppies are put on prevention immediately. All felines, regardless of age, have been tested for Feline Leukemia/FIV. Each animal receives a health check by a licensed veterinarian prior to adoption. Anything else found will be treated by our organization prior to adoption.

Ryder - Male
MinPin/Chihuahua Mix (Breed is best guess only)
DOB 11/1/2020
Current Weight 7 pounds

NO CHILDREN UNDER THE AGE OF 10
Meet Ryder. The biggest of his litter. He and his siblings were surrendered to a high kill animal control. It was a pretty scary place but they all came to Illinois in hopes of finding their forever homes. Though small he is an energetic puppy with lots of love to give. He loves to be held, playing with his siblings, (both canine and human) and his toys. He is learning all the basic puppy manners which consist of crate training, potty training. Due to his size we are asking no small children and he cannot be left home alone more then a few hours to continue his training and socialization. Are you Ryder’s forever home?. If interested please fill out an application on our website www.foreverhomedogrescueil.org


WE DO NOT DO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS
Thank you for considering the adoption of one of our rescue dogs.  We are committed to finding our rescues the perfect home. Together we can make a difference in the life of a dog.
 
The adoption process should be a fun and exciting time for families and dogs. Our goal is to place our babies in forever homes.  The potential adopter needs to be dedicated to their care and training for life. 
Understand that sharing your life with a dog can be a commitment of 15+ years. This would include feeding, exercise, training, vetting, and providing a loving home. Ask yourself, "Am I ready for this type of commitment?"  If you are ready, we are here to help.  We do have some requirements to help us find the perfect placement of our babies. 

WE ARE A FOSTER BASED RESCUE ONLY. WE DO NOT HAVE A PHYSICAL BUILDING
1.  Apply online at https://www.foreverhomedogrescueil.org
We must have an application, conduct a phone interview, and meet your entire family (including other dogs) to approve an adoption. Only a final approval for adoption can take place after a successful meet and greet. This is done by appointments only. We will not proceed with the adoption if everyone has not met the dog.  This will allow others the opportunity to adopt the dog.
2.  Adopters MUST be 21 years old.
Information on all adults/members living in the home is required
We REQUIRE you to provide proof and vet reference that all current and past pets have been kept up to date on all routine medical.
3.  Illinois law requires that all of our dogs and puppies be spayed/neutered within 30 days of adoption. In order to fully comply with this regulation and reduce the number of homeless dogs and puppies, 
4.  If you do not own your home, you must provide landlord contact information on the application and a copy of your lease that outlines the rules for dog ownership in your residence.  
Large breed dogs will not be adopted into apartment settings or where there are breed/ size restrictions.
Puppies have special needs and require a home where someone is available to care for, socialize, and give basic training.  If you are gone for more than a couple hours at a time, please consider adopting a teen or older dog.
5.  Adoption fees are $350. We accept checks or cash. (Prices are subject to change without notice).
6.  All dogs and puppies adopted through Forever Home are fully vetted with age appropriate vaccines. Keep in mind once you take possession of your newly adopted dog, any and all future medical costs or care is YOUR responsibility.
7. First time puppy/dog adopters will be required to sign up for and pay in advance a basic training class. A deposit of an extra 50.00 will be required until a class has been completed, it will then be returned. 
8. WE DO NOT DO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS

Microchipping

animal.description:
This is Annika! She was originally found as a stray roaming the streets, skinny and scared. She was safely trapped and brought to our shelter as we looked for her owners. When she first came to us she wouldn't eat, wouldn't move and would shy away from affection. We quickly found her a foster in hopes this would help her feel more comfortable. Annika has a very supportive, understanding and calm foster sibling (a Ridgeback) and she has been able to help Annika come out of her shell. 
NOW, Annika is playful, funny, goofy, sweet and loves to explore! She even has visited her foster homes vacation place up north. She enjoys sun bathing, playing with her foster sibling, sitting for treats and going for walks. 
We think Annika is about 4 years old, she is spayed, chipped, and vaccinated. If you are interested in meeting Annika, we request you visit our website www.azhartt.org and fill out her application and we will connect you and her foster family to arrange a meet and greet.

animal.description:
Are you looking for a fun-lovin' pup to spend your day playing tug and running around with? If so, Chopin is the boy for you! Chopin is an 8 month old mixed breed boy, he is currently about 43lbs and still has some filling out to do. He was originally transferred to our shelter from Louisiana as part of the hurricane disaster relief, so we do not know much about his past. In his time here, we have learned that he LOVES to play and he has a LOT of personality. Chopin has been a very sweet boy, and would love a family who has time to play with him and provide exercise and mental stimulation! Since he was transferred in from a different shelter, we aren't sure how he is with children or other animals, so if there are any children in the home or other dogs we will need to do a meet and greet to make sure everyone gets along before adoption; just to be safe! We don't know where he is on his potty-training, and he might need some time to learn in a new home. Chopin is neutered, current on his vaccinations, heartworm negative, and microchipped. Come meet this cutie patootie at the Waggin' Tails Adoption Center in Benbrook, open every day from 12-6 pm by appointment!

*Please give us a call at 817-249-3647 to schedule an appointment with us!

animal.description:
BELLA, a 3 year old Rat Terrier mix, is 1 of 4 dogs removed from a hoarding situation. Very sweet, her tail wags briskly when she sees you. Anxious to be held and give you kisses, Bella's going to be an easy girl to spoil. A bit shy in the presence of strangers, she was a little nervous (and cold) for her pictures. We tried toys, treats, whistling, all manner of distractions to get her cute ears to perk up, but to no avail. Bella is a darling and also a bit of a diva. She's treat finicky, but we've found one she favors: Vienna sausages with or without Ready-Whip! Bella's adoption fee is $175 and helps cover the cost of her spay, vaccinations, worming, monthly heart worm, flea and tick preventive, microchip and care while at CCHS. She is heart worm positive and will need treatment.

If you're interested in sponsoring a portion of Bella's heart worm treatment, you may do so by clicking on the donate button on our FB page or website and thank you!

animal.description:
Rambo - Male
MinPin/Chihuahua Mix (Breed is best guess only)
DOB 11/1/2020
Current Weight 4 pounds

NO CHILDREN UNDER THE AGE OF 10
Meet Rambo. The smallest of his litter. He and his siblings were surrendered to a high kill animal control. It was a pretty scary place but they all came to Illinois in hopes of finding their forever homes. Though small, he is an energetic puppy with lots of love to give. He loves to be held, playing with his siblings, (both canine and human) and his toys. He is learning all the basic puppy manners which consist of crate training, potty training. Due to his size we are asking no small children and he cannot be left home alone more then a few hours to continue his training and socialization. Are you Rambo’s forever home. If interested please fill out an application on our website www.foreverhomedogrescueil.org

WE DO NOT DO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS
Thank you for considering the adoption of one of our rescue dogs.  We are committed to finding our rescues the perfect home. Together we can make a difference in the life of a dog.
 
The adoption process should be a fun and exciting time for families and dogs. Our goal is to place our babies in forever homes.  The potential adopter needs to be dedicated to their care and training for life. 
Understand that sharing your life with a dog can be a commitment of 15+ years. This would include feeding, exercise, training, vetting, and providing a loving home. Ask yourself, "Am I ready for this type of commitment?"  If you are ready, we are here to help.  We do have some requirements to help us find the perfect placement of our babies. 

WE ARE A FOSTER BASED RESCUE ONLY. WE DO NOT HAVE A PHYSICAL BUILDING
1.  Apply online at https://www.foreverhomedogrescueil.org
We must have an application, conduct a phone interview, and meet your entire family (including other dogs) to approve an adoption. Only a final approval for adoption can take place after a successful meet and greet. This is done by appointments only. We will not proceed with the adoption if everyone has not met the dog.  This will allow others the opportunity to adopt the dog.
2.  Adopters MUST be 21 years old.
Information on all adults/members living in the home is required
We REQUIRE you to provide proof and vet reference that all current and past pets have been kept up to date on all routine medical.
3.  Illinois law requires that all of our dogs and puppies be spayed/neutered within 30 days of adoption. In order to fully comply with this regulation and reduce the number of homeless dogs and puppies, 
4.  If you do not own your home, you must provide landlord contact information on the application and a copy of your lease that outlines the rules for dog ownership in your residence.  
Large breed dogs will not be adopted into apartment settings or where there are breed/ size restrictions.
Puppies have special needs and require a home where someone is available to care for, socialize, and give basic training.  If you are gone for more than a couple hours at a time, please consider adopting a teen or older dog.
5.  Adoption fees are $350. We accept checks or cash. (Prices are subject to change without notice).
6.  All dogs and puppies adopted through Forever Home are fully vetted with age appropriate vaccines. Keep in mind once you take possession of your newly adopted dog, any and all future medical costs or care is YOUR responsibility.
7. First time puppy/dog adopters will be required to sign up for and pay in advance a basic training class. A deposit of an extra 50.00 will be required until a class has been completed, it will then be returned. 
8. WE DO NOT DO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS 
 
Medical included is as follows:
Spay/Neuter (age appropriate) *Forever Home uses Fox Valley Animal Welfare League in Aurora, IL
Age appropriate core vaccines
Fecal testing and deworming
Flea and tick preventative
Free 1st Vet visit at one of our participating vets
Microchipping
 
Forever Home Dog Rescue reserves the right to deny any applicant.

animal.description:
Attention please! most of your Questions about the dog and the adoption process are answered here.

Important information about Tuck:

Age: 4 months

Current size: small

Current weight: 12.8 Ibs

Sex: Male

Breed: lab mix

Color : Black and white

Anticipated size : Medium

Sterilization: Neutered

Microchipped: yes

Vaccines received : Rabies, Bordetella, Parvo, distemper, adenovirus i, adenovirus ii, and parainfluenza.

Story & background:

Tuck is a rescue from San Bernardino. He was found roaming with his brother (will be posted for adoption soon) on a dirt road. There was a great rally for dirt bikers on that road at the time the puppies were found. Our volunteers were concerned about the saftey of the puppies especially that they can be easily hit by dirt bikers. Therefore, the volunteers hurried to capture the puppies with some treats. This motivated the puppies to come closer to our volunteers. The puppies seemed very malnourished and dehydrated. At that point, our volunteer reached out to our corporate office to describe the situation. Immediately, our corporate office booked an appointment with a trusted veterinarian to help assess the health of the puppies. The veterinarian ended up prescribing them some vitamins and supplements to help compensate for the nutrients they lacked. The rescue then assigned the task of taking care of the puppies to one of our trusted fosters to help socialize them and help them gain weight through a healthy diet. The rescue has provided the puppies with all the required vaccines. They also all got Neutered. 

Behavioral wise, the puppies get along with larger and smaller breeds of dogs. We have not had them around cats. However, since they are still young puppies, we believe that they are trainable to work with cats. They also do great around people and children. They are also exceptionally smart and so cuddly.

PetEmber Animal Rescue is a California 501 (C) (3) charitable non-profit organization that does not receive any governmental funding and relies only on the donations of the public to help provide urgent care for abandoned, neglected, and abused dogs and puppies. All donations are tax-deductible. Our rescue is in continuous improvement and we strive to cope with all the technologies of the era to help provide better services to our customers and better care for our rescued dogs. When adopting a dog from PetEmber, you receive a well-rounded healthy dog that is up to date on all vaccines since all proceeds are directed to provide a supreme veterinarian care, nutrition, and training for the dogs we have. These proceeds are also used to help care for other senior, disabled, or hard to adopt dogs due to behavioral issues. The adopter receives a complete health record for his/her adopted dog on site at the time of the adoption. Necessary paperwork such as the rabies certificate, Spay/neuter certificate, vaccination record, and a copy of the adoption agreement are all handed to the adopter at the time of the adoption. These documents help the adopters in the process of licensing the dog or registering the dog as an emotional support animal (ESA). All dogs posted for adoption are 100% ready for their forever homes.

If you are interested in adopting any of our adoptable dogs, we created an online adoption application that better works with Safari or google chrome browsers.

Link to the adoption application :

www.petember.com/adoption-application

Please fill and submit your adoption application as soon as possible. We receive hundreds of applications for each dog. Submitting your application earlier and filling all the required fields will help prioritize your adoption application. We review all application but will not have enough assistance to help provide reply on each individual application. Therefore, if your adoption application is approved, you should hear from us within 24 hours after your application is submitted. Please be sure you are ready for immediate meet and greet. 

Stay safe during this Pandemic.

animal.description: Woof, woof! I'm so excited you're thinking about adopting a new fur-ever family member! Here are a few things that may help you with your big decision. First, dogs just want to be happy and feel loved. Living inside and being a part of the family is really important to us. A lot of the things you need as humans to stay happy and healthy, us dogs need too. We depend on you for things like vet visits, nutritious food, clean water, social and play time with people and other pets, training classes, toys, and of course, lots of love and attention! Regular baths, nail trims and grooming help us to look and feel our best, while monthly flea and heartworm prevention help us to stay healthy. Did you know that depending on our size and breed, dogs can live up to 20 years? Just think of the wonderful life we could have together!

animal.description:
Meet Cassie! Cassie is a two year old Lab/Border Collie mix and she is looking for her fur-ever home! Cassie gets along well with other dogs, but does chase cats. She knows how to sit, lay down, and is house-trained! Cassie is a love bug and is affectionate with her people. We think she would be a wonderful fit for someone who likes to be active and would like a partner for outdoor adventures! Contact BRHS to set up a meet and greet with Cassie! 

Most of our dogs are currently in shelter - but some are in foster homes.  If you would like to see a specific dog, feel free to contact us to see if they are in shelter or in foster care!  Dogs in shelter are available to visit or adopt daily.  IF a dog is in a foster home, they come in on Saturdays from 11:00am to 4:00pm. Arrangements can be made to have specific dogs brought in during the week- just give us a call or email to see if the dog you are interested in is in a foster home and set up a meeting time if necessary.

Our adoption fees include the following: all of our dogs/puppies are current on vaccinations (DHPP and Rabies if over 3 months of age) at the point of adoption, dewormed, heartworm tested and current on preventative, microchipped, treated for fleas/ticks and are spayed or neutered. Our large dog adoption fee is generally $150 + tax. Our small dog and puppy adoption fee is generally $250 + tax. Adoption fees may vary in special circumstances. Due to space limitations, we do not hold dogs.

Because we are on a busy street, we require that all dogs leaving the shelter be in a carrier or on leash. All pets remain up for adoption until an approved application is processed and their adoption fee paid. Adoptions will stop a half hour before we close, at 5:30pm M-F and 3:30pm Saturday.

animal.description:
Feast your eyes upon this gorgeous lady, Pepper! Pepper is a 6 year old American Blue Heeler/ Australian Shepherd mix who is looking for a furrever home to roam around in. Unfortunately, She was surrendered to the shelter because she didn't mesh well with the current doggos in the home, so with that being said Pepper would need to be the only furchild in the home. This girl is one of the sweetest and smartest little ladies you'll ever meet. She know multiple commands such as sit, right and left paw, down, roll over and many more. Her previous owners said she is great with children and from what we have seen we also agree. She is a very calm and obedient girl, but also still has the drive of a cattle dog. Therefore, she would be a great companion for hiking, jogging, or even just chilling on the beach. Her previous owners also mentioned she is crate trained and housetrained. She has a lot of love in her heart and is looking for someone to share that with. Pepper is current on her vaccines, microchipped, heartworm test negative, and spayed so she is ready to join your family today! Come meet this fantastic canine at the Waggin' Tails Adoption Center in Benbrook, we are open everyday from 12-6pm.

**Please call 817-249-3647 to schedule an appointment today.

Mills is about 3 years old and weighs about 50 pounds.

If you're interested in meeting Mills, please visit our website to learn about our adoption process and to fill out an application, www.gatewaypets.org/adopt

Gateway Pet Guardians is proud to offer a variety of mixed breed dogs available for adoption. animal.description:
Age: 2 Months (as of 1/24/2021)
Weight: ~ 8 lbs (as of 1/24/2021)

This dog has been spayed/neutered, is up to date on shots, on heartworm preventative and is microchipped.

The HappyDays pups are here to bring joy to your life!

These puppies are playful, even-tempered, and very affectionate! The litter is three adorable girls - Marion, Joanie, and Lori Beth and four handsome boys - Fonzie, Howard, Chachi, and Richie. We are thinking these cute babies are an Australian Shepherd and Carolina Dog mix. This litter is named after the classic tv show Happy Days that aired in the 1970s - 1980s. The pups love all people including the two teenagers that are living in their foster home. They are friendly and playful with each other but we don't know how they are with new dogs, but given that they are so young we anticipate that they would get along with a new dog sibling well. Their current foster home has two cats and they seem interested and playful when they encounter them but we can't guarantee they will do well as they grow older with co-habitating cats. They love toys and are happy to chill with a squeaky ball or fun chew toy when not playing with you, and t

heir favorite play styles are wrestling or a fun round of chase.

The pups are pretty quiet but you might hear them bark when playing.
Though a fenced yard is an ideal place for your puppy to romp and play safely, if that's not an option then lots of daily leash walks and opportunities to play off leash is the next best thing.

Puppies are a lot of work and require a strong commitment to teaching them obedience and socializing them with other dogs and people. A well-mannered, obedient dog will be welcomed most anywhere you take him/her.
As the pups are still so young, they haven't yet started on potty training, crate training or leash training but think they will pick up these skills quickly as they seem very smart. All the HappyDays pups are eager to please, toy and treat motivated, so puppy training classes will be lots of fun!

Fonzie would love to find a forever family that has lots of time and patience to raise a puppy properly, and who has lots of extra time for loving and cuddles. Think Fonzie (or one of his littermates) may be perfect furry addition to your family? Fill out an application today!

HappyDays pup's Backstory: These pups came from an unplanned litter in Arkansas and have been in SOS foster care since birth. They are getting ready to make the ride to New England to meet their forever families!

Adoption Fee: $585

To apply for this dog, fill out an adoption application on our website: www.sosarl.org/aa/

**Additional info you should know - For most of our dogs, we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each of our dogs as an individual and do our best to describe and place them based on personality not breed label. Some dogs may not yet be in New England, nor ready for immediate adoption. There may be additional vetting, quarantine, waiting periods and/or fees depending upon your state of residence. If you have questions or concerns on any of this, you can discuss this with your Adoption Counselor.

animal.description:
Cosmo is a super sweet male Australian Shepherd/Border Collie mix. His original owners surrendered him as an Aussie/Border mix, but we think he may have something else in him too... possibly Great Dane. Born on 3/25/20, he's 10 months old and around 60 pounds now. Cosmo is housebroken, crate trained, dog/kid friendly (though he's still learning his size), and happy-go-lucky. He's a smart boy, food motivated, and eager to please. He has normal puppy energy for his age and his breed mix, and he really enjoys playing with other dogs. He'd love active adopters who will exercise him, train him, stimulate his brain, and a fenced in yard of his own for a fun game of fetch. He might even be pretty good in agility or other dog sports. Cosmo is a great pup and will make an excellent companion for a very lucky adoptive family. No apartments. Please do not apply if you do not understand the Aussie/Border breeds and their needs. He is fully vetted, neutered, microchipped, and ready for adoption! 
To help pay for vet bills and care (transportation, food, toys, etc..) a $300 donation is requested at the time of adoption. All of our adoptions are contingent upon an approved application, home visit, reference check, obedience training agreement, and signing of adoption contract. All our dogs are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, and microchipped before adoption. Our dogs are companion animals that live indoors as part of your family. Please do not apply if your plan is to have them as outside dogs, garage dogs, porch dogs or outside kennel dogs. We do not ship dogs. All of our dogs are in private foster homes. We are not a shelter with hours. A visit can be arranaged after an adoption questionnaire has been filled out and sent in. Please try email first. We are all volunteers that work so we can not easily take or make phone calls.

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please download and complete an Adoption Questionnaire from our website and email Nora at NoraL@k-9lifesavers.org
You can learn about the adoption process and find a Word, PDF and ONLINE version of the questionnaire by visiting: http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/howtoadopt/.
Dog's Name: Tiny Tim
Estimated Breed : Chihuahua Mix
Approximate Age: 2-3 years
Approximate Weight: approx. 18-20 lbs
Currently Living at: Boarding
Adoption Fee: $300
DOG'S DESCRIPTION
Tiny Tim is an adorable little guy looking for his forever home. Tiny Tim will need a quiet, calm, and nurturing home. He is nervous around new people, especially males. He has nipped in the past when scared, so his adopters will need to move slow with him and give him time to open up and trust. Tiny Tim would be happiest in a single family home with a yard in a quiet neighborhood. He needs a mature household (no young kids). He doesn't know how to walk well on leash and will most likely need some work in the housetraining department. If you feel you have the right home environment for this cutie, then Tiny Tim is ready to come home with you and be showered with love. Once he learns to trust, we know he will make a wonderful companion!
Your new pet will require a refresher in house-training. K-9 Lifesavers strongly recommends all new adopters enroll their new pet into obedience training. This provides for an easier transition into a new home, ensures the dog remains well socialized, and helps form a bond between the dog and the new family.
Adoption fees cover basic vetting, spay/neuter surgery (for dogs over 6 months old), rabies, distemper/parvo vaccinations, treatment for worms, heartworm testing, monthly heartworm prevention and monthly flea/tick prevention (while the animal is in our care), and transport costs from high-kill shelter. Please note that on average, K-9 Lifesavers spend significantly more on each dog than their adoption fee. Adoption fee for HW positive dog also covers heartworm treatment at our partner vets.
Foster Program: Foster homes provide for the temporary care of a rescue until the dog is placed into a loving, forever home. For more information on becoming a foster parent, and our Foster Program, visit http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/foster/ or email our Foster Coordinator at foster@k-9lifesavers.org
Sponsor Me! Make a tax-deductible donation today by visiting us at http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/donate/ . Donations help us offset boarding costs and additional medical treatment for those dogs who need it. K-9 Lifesavers receives NO federal funding and survive with your generous support!
For more information on K-9 Lifesavers, or to view a complete listing of all our Adoptable Dogs, visit our website at www.k-9lifesavers.org.
Please "like" our Facebook Page for the most current events and new dogs.
Thank you for considering a rescue dog!

animal.description:
Meet Rebekah!

Rebekah is a friend to all and assumes all are friends to her. This little pup is the definition of “puppy”. She is ready to go when you are and would love an active home to keep up with her active lifestyle. She’s a lover of people and other dogs, so some kids or dogs in her forever home would be a huge bonus to her. Maaaaybe some older kids or bigger dogs. She is a puppy after all and has that puppy exuberance for life.

She has a love/hate relationship with the crate, sometimes it’s awesome, sometimes it’s a prison meant to prevent her from enjoying life. Keep her on a schedule though and she is fully potty trained (girl knows when she needs to go, keep up with the program)

Rebekah is a 3 month old pit mix. She is spayed, up to date with age appropriate vaccines, and microchipped

Her adoption fee is $200

Behavior evaluations should be considered as a snapshot of the behavior of the dog at this point in time; JHS believes all dog families need to be prepared to invest time and energy into training as well as provide common sense management of their new dog. We always encourage family to do some research on the breeds or mixes of breeds prior to adoption as many can have some unique characteristics that may or may not fit into their families. Always remember that the majority of dogs at our shelter have been exposed to or may have kennel cough. Kennel cough is contagious to other dogs, please talk to your vet if you have any questions about kennel cough prior to adoption. Please ask your adoption counselor at time of adoption if you have any unanswered questions regarding illnesses and treatments of the path that you are adopting. For more information about this dog or any others at our Shelter, please visit www.joplinhumane.org. We are the Joplin Humane Society in Joplin, Missouri. 417-623-3642

Experience with large bully breeds is a plus. Having another dog in the home is a plus.

animal.description:
Duffy - Male
Lab/Hound Mix (Breed is best guess only)
DOB 10/21/2020
Current weight 16lbs

FENCED IN YARD RECOMMENDED 
Not recommending homes with small children due to typical puppy jumping and nipping

Meet Duffy. He is 1 of 7 siblings surrendered to the shelter, so they all came to Illinois to find a forever home. Though from Arkansas he loves the snow and his toys. He is an energetic puppy who adores attention and a lot of love to give. He does great with everyone, kids and other dogs. He is learning basic puppy manners, crate training and potty training all of which are going well. He will need someone home (not left alone more then a few hours) to continue with these basics and socialization skills. With love and patience he will make a wonderful addition to any home.

WE DO NOT DO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS
Thank you for considering the adoption of one of our rescue dogs.  We are committed to finding our rescues the perfect home. Together we can make a difference in the life of a dog.
 
The adoption process should be a fun and exciting time for families and dogs. Our goal is to place our babies in forever homes.  The potential adopter needs to be dedicated to their care and training for life. 
Understand that sharing your life with a dog can be a commitment of 15+ years. This would include feeding, exercise, training, vetting, and providing a loving home. Ask yourself, "Am I ready for this type of commitment?"  If you are ready, we are here to help.  We do have some requirements to help us find the perfect placement of our babies. 

WE ARE A FOSTER BASED RESCUE ONLY. WE DO NOT HAVE A PHYSICAL BUILDING
1.  Apply online at https://www.foreverhomedogrescueil.org
We must have an application, conduct a phone interview, and meet your entire family (including other dogs) to approve an adoption. Only a final approval for adoption can take place after a successful meet and greet. This is done by appointments only. We will not proceed with the adoption if everyone has not met the dog.  This will allow others the opportunity to adopt the dog.
2.  Adopters MUST be 21 years old.
Information on all adults/members living in the home is required
We REQUIRE you to provide proof and vet reference that all current and past pets have been kept up to date on all routine medical.
3.  Illinois law requires that all of our dogs and puppies be spayed/neutered within 30 days of adoption. In order to fully comply with this regulation and reduce the number of homeless dogs and puppies, 
4.  If you do not own your home, you must provide landlord contact information on the application and a copy of your lease that outlines the rules for dog ownership in your residence.  
Large breed dogs will not be adopted into apartment settings or where there are breed/ size restrictions.
Puppies have special needs and require a home where someone is available to care for, socialize, and give basic training.  If you are gone for more than a couple hours at a time, please consider adopting a teen or older dog.
5.  Adoption fees are $350. We accept checks or cash. (Prices are subject to change without notice).
6.  All dogs and puppies adopted through Forever Home are fully vetted with age appropriate vaccines. Keep in mind once you take possession of your newly adopted dog, any and all future medical costs or care is YOUR responsibility.

animal.description:
**Please read Ranger DOTUS's entire profile, which includes a link to the adoption application. Thank you!** 

Meet the Presidential Pups litter! They are all named for a previous or current DOTUS (Dog of The United States!) At 6 weeks old, Ranger (named for George H. W. Bush's beloved pup) is a big lovable pupper. He weighs 9 pounds.  He spends most of his day sleeping and playing with his sisters. Dad hails from Tenneessee but unclear what breed, we would guess shepherd or labrador. Mom is the cuddliest 28 lbs you will ever meet! Also a mix, mom appears to be part beagle and part golden retriever. These pups are also cuddly, just like their mama! With proper training and frequent exercise, these pups will be a fantastic addition to your family!

All dogs are up to date on vaccinations and spayed/neutered at the time of adoption.  Due to the young age of this puppy, he/she is not housebroken or trained unless otherwise specially indicated. All puppies require professional training to become the best family member they can be.

To adopt or learn more about Ranger DOTUS, you must fill out an adoption application. To find the application, copy and paste this URL into your browser: WWW.GDRNE.COM/ADOPTION-APPLICATION [Adoption Fee: $550]  **  PLEASE READ: If a dog is listed, then s/he is currently available for adoption. Their information is correct to the best of our abilities and the information we have been given as of the day of posting. Please note, GDRNE does not guarantee the breed of any dog or puppy unless stated that we have run DNA. All breeds listed are educated estimates. Our dogs are rescued from various situations. It is most likely that both their parents were strays and even if not, mixes of some sort and that their grandparents were mixes as well. The dog may have some genetic material of an American Staffordshire Terrier (pit bull). The dogs are usually mixes of many breeds, making them a breed all their own - a True and adorable American MUTT. If you are interested in this dog, you must submit an application. Great Dog is not a shelter so there is no building you can visit. Our dogs live in private foster homes until adopted. To learn more about our *shelterless* rescue, adoption fees, and procedures, review the list of Frequently Asked Questions on our website at WWW.GDRNE.COM.

Dex - Male
Lab/Retriever Mix (Breed is best guess only)
DOB 11/2/2020
Current weight 20lbs

FENCED IN YARD RECOMMENDED 
Meet Dex . He was abandoned and surrendered to the shelter, so he came to Illinois to find a forever home. Though from Arkansas he loves the snow and his toys. He is an energetic puppy who adores attention and a lot of love to give. He does great with everyone, kids and other dogs. He is learning basic puppy manners, crate training and potty training all of which are going well. He will need someone home (not left alone more then a few hours) to continue with these basics and socialization skills. With love and patience he will make a wonderful addition to any home.

WE DO NOT DO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS
Thank you for considering the adoption of one of our rescue dogs.  We are committed to finding our rescues the perfect home. Together we can make a difference in the life of a dog.
 
The adoption process should be a fun and exciting time for families and dogs. Our goal is to place our babies in forever homes.  The potential adopter needs to be dedicated to their care and training for life. 
Understand that sharing your life with a dog can be a commitment of 15+ years. This would include feeding, exercise, training, vetting, and providing a loving home. Ask yourself, "Am I ready for this type of commitment?"  If you are ready, we are here to help.  We do have some requirements to help us find the perfect placement of our babies. 

WE ARE A FOSTER BASED RESCUE ONLY. WE DO NOT HAVE A PHYSICAL BUILDING
1.  Apply online at https://www.foreverhomedogrescueil.org
We must have an application, conduct a phone interview, and meet your entire family (including other dogs) to approve an adoption. Only a final approval for adoption can take place after a successful meet and greet. This is done by appointments only. We will not proceed with the adoption if everyone has not met the dog.  This will allow others the opportunity to adopt the dog.
2.  Adopters MUST be 21 years old.
Information on all adults/members living in the home is required
We REQUIRE you to provide proof and vet reference that all current and past pets have been kept up to date on all routine medical.
3.  Illinois law requires that all of our dogs and puppies be spayed/neutered within 30 days of adoption. In order to fully comply with this regulation and reduce the number of homeless dogs and puppies, 
4.  If you do not own your home, you must provide landlord contact information on the application and a copy of your lease that outlines the rules for dog ownership in your residence.  
Large breed dogs will not be adopted into apartment settings or where there are breed/ size restrictions.
Puppies have special needs and require a home where someone is available to care for, socialize, and give basic training.  If you are gone for more than a couple hours at a time, please consider adopting a teen or older dog.
5.  Adoption fees are $350. We accept checks or cash. (Prices are subject to change without notice).
6.  All dogs and puppies adopted through Forever Home are fully vetted with age appropriate vaccines. Keep in mind once you take possession of your newly adopted dog, any and all future medical costs or care is YOUR responsibility.
7. First time puppy/dog adopters will be required to sign up for and pay in advance a basic training class. A deposit of an extra 50.00 will be required until a class has been completed, it will then be returned. 
8. WE DO NOT DO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS 
 
Medical included is as follows:
Spay/Neuter (age appropriate) *Forever Home uses Fox Valley Animal Welfare League in Aurora, IL
Age appropriate core vaccines
Fecal testing and deworming
Flea and tick preventative

We can't believe Lady hasn't been scooped up yet! Her fosters have been so impressed with her .

She still does have some anxiety when there is a lot going on around her (public park on a nice day) but consistent work and lots of treats has made a huge improvement. She would be a wonderful companion for a family.

animal.description:
Tinsel is a love! He adores his person and everyone he meets. He wags and leans in for pets. He is such a resilient boy despite being blind. I have learned that non tipping water bowls and food bowls help him. He really uses his nose, sense of smell and high stepping prance to navigate.

Tinsel has just recently learned to play with toys and prances proudly with his favorite in his mouth. It seems tennis balls are his favorite and I can absolutely see him learning to fetch with his person.

Tinsel is house trained and crate trained. He gets along well with other dogs and cats. He is good with children. Tinsel does well on leash and does not pull. He has been a perfect patient at the vet and does so well.

Tinsel is around 5 years old and weighs about 70 pounds. Tinsel is a good boy who just wants love. He does well once he understands his new environment and guides very well by a collar or by following my steps and voice.

Tinsel loves a dog bed but his favorite place is to be beside you on the couch. I do not crate him. I do keep him in a room gated off with a dog bed when I leave and at night and he does super. He is a super sweet pleaser who will be such a gift to anyone who opens their heart to him, despite his blindness

Tinsel doesn’t jump and is well-behaved. He has only growled if startled out of a deep sleep by a pouncing puppy. Otherwise, he never makes a peep; although he cried once to go out to potty.

Tinsel is looking for home where he will be an adored family member and accepted despite his blindness. Respectful kids of any age will be great, he adored the 7 year old he met here. I think pouncing toddlers may scare him if he is asleep. No noises seem to scare him, he really is a very chill, good energy, happy pup.

He does have some allergy issues but is responding amazing to treatment the vet did. I also switched his protein source to lamb and that may be helping too.

He eats about 1.5 cups of Iams Lamb adult AM and PM. He loves all cookies, cheese and sometimes I add pumpkin to his food and he loves that too.

If you are interested in Tinsel and are an approved adopter, please contact your Adoption Coordinator to be added to Tinsel’s list. If you are not yet approved you can find our adoption guidelines and application at:  www.savealabrescue.org

animal.description:
Buffy was found in the streets in Southeast Houston. Her finder spent 2 weeks looking for her owner, but nobody claimed her, so she asked for our help in finding a great home for Buffy. Buffy is 1 year old and weighs about 15 pounds. The vet says she has some Pomeranian in her, but is a definite mix. Buffy is very sweet and playful. She would love another young dog to play with in her forever home. She's been doing good with pottying outside using a petdoor or being taken out regularly. Buffy would try to back out of her collar or harness when we got her, but she's doing better now with walking on leash. She likes to chase cats if they run, but is never aggressive with them. Buffy likes older children that will play with her. She has been a delight to foster. She's a very loving girl and would love a forever home.

In order to adopt, you need to send an e-mail to rescue@secondchancepoms.org asking for an application.  After you send this back, we will check references and someone will visit you in your home to discuss adoption.  We ask a donation of $425 for adults, which includes an applicable Texas sales tax, and $475 for puppies, which includes an applicable Texas sales tax.  This covers shots, spay/neuter, and any medical treatment, such as de-worming. We do not ship our pomeranians, but an out-of-state adoption can still happen if the adopter comes to the Houston, TX area to pick up their pom.
