animal.description:
Oh, where do I begin with my precious girl Zola? She has so many beautiful sides to her that are wonderful. There's the energetic, wiggle butt, who barks excitedly when I come home from work. There's the quiet more laid back Zola when I'm on the couch watching a movie. There's the attentive at my feet Zola while I cook dinner. Zola does have a bit of energy but it's mostly when I come home from work. She is kenneled when I leave the house so I'm sure she's ready to get out and play as soon as I walk through the door! I have a large yard so Zola gets plenty of time to run around and get her energy out! Once she's done running around and playing, she'll come in and plop down and relax. Zola is a very friendly and love-able dog. She is friendly to all and has a heart of gold.

Zola does chew. On shoes! She has ruined quite a few pairs of mine and my children's so I have to keep them locked up in the closet. You’ve been warned! This happy girl is a bit clumsy when she is let out of her kennel and does a spin, dance, twirl move which tends knock over anything in her path; almost like she's a miniature tornado.

have so enjoyed having Zola with me. Zola came to me, during a difficult time in my life last year, and I found myself leaning heavily on her gentle soul. She's attentive to my needs and was always right there to snuggle with me when I needed her. Even my cat, who is a recluse when it comes to my other dogs, snuggled with Zola on the couch or bed. Animals know a gentle soul when they meet one and Zola's is so full of love to give. Zola has eyes that cross a bit when she looks up at me with love in her eyes and I found myself falling more and more in love with those big, brown, crossed eyes every day. 

Watch your bag of dog food! I was so confused for months as to why it always seemed like I had less and less dog food than I remembered, and at one point even felt alarmed at how bad my memory was becoming, until one day I caught Zola with her head shoved all the way down the bag of dog food happily chomping away. She didn't even have the decency to look ashamed when I caught her. She just looked at me with her tail wagging, crunching away at her endless buffet. I now keep it in a large closed container. 

Zola is around 3 years old and weighs about 60 pounds. She is crate trained and house trained. Zola is good with kids, other dogs and cats as well. 

To the person that ends up with Zola, your life will be for the better having her contagious bubbly energy and love radiate throughout your home. I was beyond blessed having her here with me and the wonderful laughs she brought to my family. Her presence will be greatly missed but I can't wait to see where the next chapter of her life will take her. Best wishes!

If you are interested in Zola and are an approved adopter, please contact your Adoption Coordinator to be added to Zola’s list. If you are not yet approved you can find our adoption guidelines and application at:  www.savealabrescue.org

Zola is fostered in RI

animal.description:
Millie Jane is the typical Chihuaha breed; timid, flighty, shy, protective of her home, but dog friendly. She was born in March 2020 and weighs 7 pounds. She is potty trained, crate trained, and loves to ride in a car. She is working on leash manners along with social skills. She is very submissive and will submissive pees on occassion. Millie Jane loves to be by her female fosters side at all times but will lay with foster dad as well. Her loving, wiggly, crawling, underbite self, is perfect for the Chichuaha lover! Her favorite thing to do is to take all the toys out of the toy box and relocate them throughout the house. She still has a lot of puppy in her. She will eat what is on the floor including dust bunnies, leaves, or anything else she can swallow so kleenex and trash cans need to be put up before leaving her for a long period of time. She is not destructive by any means just a little mischievious! 

She will require a Chihauaha experienced home with understanding it takes at least three days for her to trust hand and voice commands. She needs to go at her own pace and requires the adopter to understand this. She can be mouthly so a home with no children is a must. She can be fierce when she thinks she is in harms way and will protect herself. Once she knows you mean her no harm and you have chicken she is your shadow!!! She is so sweet and loving.
animal.name: Millie Jane

animal.description:
Quarantining and need a nap buddy? Look no further, we have your girl! Marathon runner looking for a long-distance partner, nope she ain't got time for that! Daisy is a middle age (estimated at about 7) retired mother who has raised her kids and now just needs a long vacation, several hundred naps, a few good books, and maybe a nice red. Daisy is looking for a nap partner who will share the covers and maybe throw another log on the fire for her. She is great with kids, cats, and dogs who realize she doesn't want to play but is totally down to be the little spoon. She is a little thing weighing in under 20 pounds.

 

Daisy is fully crate trained, low energy and working on her potty skills. On warm days she likes to go outside, but on cold days getting up from her warm spot to go outside isn't really on her agenda. Maybe a nice warm coat or some homemade mittens could entice her to stray from her busy schedule of napping and dreaming. Daisy really is a dream herself and will make some chill, low-key person an amazing forever companion. If your couch has a small spot left to share for this sweet gal, she would love to keep it warm for you. Daisy is spayed, microchipped, and up to date on shots. Her adoption fee is $275, and you can apply to adopt her at www.rescueofhope.com/adoption-application

animal.description:
Merry Clara Hippopotamus was the 25th dog rescued in 2020 by Sketchy Mutts and Underdogs. It was just before Christmas, so she needed a special holiday name. Where did Hippopotamus come from....? Just look at her!

This cute little hippo was taken to the shelter as a skinny, itchy, scabby stray with swollen feet and bilateral ear infections. Her feet were so painful that she had to be carried outside and she would only walk short distances before she would sit down and hold her feet up. Her ears were cropped short, and she appeared to have had several litters of puppies. The rescue loved her at first sight!

In her foster home, Merry got lots of love, good food, medication for her skin and ears, medicated baths and lots of fancy new sweaters to keep her warm while she healed. Now she’s ready to find a forever home of her own.

The sad, tired dog who came to the shelter is now a spirited, spunky girl who greets every human she meets like they’re her long lost best friend. She loves stuffed animals, cuddling on the couch under a blanket and car rides. Her feet are much less painful, but she does have a condition called hyperkeratosis possibly due to an  untreated illness when she was a puppy. She’s gone from needing to be carried outside to enjoying two mile walks with her foster mom!

Merry likes one of the dogs in her foster home, but is not too fond of the other one. Most likely, with proper introduction, she would be fine with a big, friendly, dog who would be tolerant while she figures things out. On walks, Merry is very focused on the neighborhood cats and small dogs she has seen, and would probably do best in a home without small animals. While foster mom is at work, Merry stays in a room with baby gates and mostly sleeps on the couch all day. She is house trained, but will use a potty pad if she can’t wait until foster mom comes home. Merry has learned so much, and is thriving in her foster home. She will be a great companion for one lucky family.
animal.name: Merry Hippopotamus

animal.description:
Pablo is a 10yr old, 10lb Mini Poodle boy. Talk about a face you cant say no to! Pablo is an adorable, affectionate, and special companion. Pablo is completely deaf and since he cant hear his humans, he likes to stay close to you - whether snuggled up in your lap on the couch or next to you in bed at night. He will be your shadow and follow you closely wherever you go, often standing right at your feet. This little guy will love his person so much, he does not want you to leave - so a home where someone is home more often than not is a definite must have for him. He walks well outside on a leash and is comfortable riding in the car. He is kind, mild-mannered, and oh so sweet. Pablo is on heart medication he takes twice daily, which costs around $60 per month. Due to his mellow nature and close attachment to his humans, he would do best in a home that is calm like he is without children. Pablo has shown great house-training manners when kept to a schedule. He is good with other dogs, and while there aren't any cats in his foster home, we think that he would be ok with them as well. 

If Pablo sounds like the new lap dog youve been looking for, please visit our website www.PoodleandPoochRescue.org where you will find the application to adopt. Pablo is up to date on his vaccines, neutered, heartworm negative, and microchipped. His adoption donation is $250.

animal.description:
We finally know the answer to the age old question "Who's a Good Boy?" It is Sir Sammie!

He is such a good boy, sweet and eager to please.

All we know about his background is that his human passed on, and he still has so much love to give!

Sir Sammie asks for very little; just a comfortable place to rest, as close to his human as possible, some good food, and fresh air each day.

He is interested in, and polite to, our personal dogs, but respects their signals that they are not as interested in him. He has such good manners!

Sammie is very well house trained, and lets you know when he needs to go out. Due to his maturity, he sometimes needs to go as often as every 3-4 hours, but he does sleep through the night.

He enjoys walking on a leash, but should only walk for short distances, especially in the heat. He likes to ride in a wagon or a pram for additional fresh air when his short legs and senior body dictate that he should not walk further.

Sir Sammie Loves:

Sharing a chair and snuggling next to his human.
Listening to the "Easy listening" music station on Comcast, and the Divinity of Dogs album by George Skaroulis
Watermelon, Pupperoni, fish flavored Food

He does NOT like:

Peanut Butter or Thunderstorms!

Sir Sammie has some aches and pains, but is very stoic about them, unless he is picked up wrong. He will let you know if you are unwittingly causing pain.

Angel Among Us is treating his pain with joint supplements and pain meds, and he is already starting to feel better. The Angels are also arranging additional medical evaluation soon to make sure that all of his health issues are addressed, so he is only available for pre-adoption at this time.

Sir Sammie will make a wonderful, loving companion for a loving human. He will be fine as an only dog as long as he has human companionship, but has demonstrated that he can get along fine with other gentle dogs. We do not know about cats.

For inquiries, email inquiry@angelsrescue.org

An Adoption Application for this dog can be found and submitted online at http://www.angelsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-forms

Please be sure to like our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/angelsrescue.

*Some of our animals receive a high volume of applications, and we strive to select the best home for each animal. However, we have many wonderful homeless pets available.

animal.description:
This little cutie patootie is Coco, a 6 1/2 year old Chihuahua/ Pug mix that is looking for the perfect home to retire in! Sadly, Coco was surrendered because he wasn't getting along with the other pets in the home, that being said, he will have to be the only animal in his new home. Coco really is a character of a dog, he lights up any room he walks into with his underbite alone! Coco loves running around outside, getting treats, and curling up next to his favorite person! Coco's previous owner's did say that he does not get along with smaller children, so a home with older children that know how to handle dogs would be best for him. Coco does not like having his paws touched at all, so you will have to work with him on trimming his nails. Sadly, in his previous home Coco spent almost all of his time outside, so he is still adjusting to his new life indoors, but is loving the AC and soft blankies! Coco loves getting tummy rubs and will even lay on his side, with his belly up in case you feel like giving him a tummy rub at any time! This sweet boy is current on his vaccines, heartworm negative, microchipped and neutered so he is ready to come home today! He is still adjusting to the new potty routine in the shelter, so he will need some time to adjust to the routine in his new home; so please be patient with him. Coco is available at the Waggin' Tails Adoption Center in Benbrook, open every day from 12-6 pm, by appointment!

*Please give us a call at 817-249-3647 to schedule an appointment!

Hi everyone! Im Brutus! I am a nearly 2 year old Great Pyrenees/ Border Collie mix and I am looking for my forever home!! 

I am a super sweet guy that absolutely loves kids and I would love to go to a home with some for me to play with!!! I am house trained and I love the snow!!! I would love to have a fenced in yard so I can run around in the snow but a fence is not required!! I am a playful guy and would be great with other dogs that are about my size or larger but I can be a little rough with dogs that are smaller than me! I have not been around cats. 

I really LOVE being with my family so when they leave the home for long periods of time, I do suffer with a good bit of separation anxiety. Because of that I am required to go to a home with a family that has atleast one family member that is home for majority of the day!!! (even after the covid restrictions are lifted!!!) 

My adoption fee is $300 and includes all age appropriate vaccinations/ microchip & neuter! If you think Id make the perfect addition to your family, please fill out an application on the website crossyourpaws.com - once your application has been reviewed/approved you will be contacted to set up an meet and greet!! 
 if you have an application already on file and would like Brutus attached to it, please send us a PM! DO NOT EMAIL! Thank you! 

I cannot wait to meet you! 
- Brutus

animal.description:
Buddy was abandoned by his owner and was left to roam around a small Missouri town. Some folks in town were kind to Buddy, some were not. Thank goodness a kind woman, who had been feeding Buddy, called BBRH to help. He had been spending time near her home and was even playing with her kids. This is how he got his name. The kids called him Buddy. 

Buddy is in really good shape for being a stray for a while. We think he is 1-2 year old tri-colored male beagle. After getting a bath, we found his fur is very soft. Buddy appears to be house trained, only having one accident since living with his foster family and that was after we left the doggy door close. Speaking of doggy door, he learned how to use it quickly so he seems quite smart.

Buddy didnt sleep much when he first came to us. We believe this was from having to sleep with one eye open out on the street. He has relaxed and is getting more rest, becoming more comfortable with us each day. He is still timid and scared by loud noises, but very, very friendly. We get lots of kisses from him. He does have some separation anxiety which is understandable after being abandon. He doesnt like the kennel. He doesnt seem to be a chewer. He tried to dig under and bite through a fence, but he was trying to get to his foster dad, who hes become attached to.

Buddy plays well with other dogs and seems to be ok with kids. We dont know how he is with cats. He has been good on car rides. He eats fast, but not sure if this is from not always having a regular meal or just being a beagle.

Buddy is neutered, heart worm negative, up to date on all vaccinations, and chipped. His adoption fee is $350 and being fostered in the Kansas City area. You can apply for Buddy B at www.bassetandbeagle.org

animal.description:
After 659 days in rescue we were ELATED when she was adopted! We even waited weeks to make sure that it was going to stick before announcing. The day after we announced her adoption we were told it wasn't going to work. Scarlett has lived a life the past 659 days in a strict routine as she isn't dog friendly, so she was on a crate and rotate schedule. She was out in a new home and just was given too much freedom
And change too fast and became overwhelmed. Scarlett needs a home, without kids (it had the largest negative impact on her relationship with the kids), that can take it slow. We REALLY want to avoid having to bring her back here to her previous foster to crate and rotate again. Can anyone help Scarlett?? 

Scarlett Josephine

Located in the Gillette WY area
Bulldog/Staffordshire Terrier/Boxer aka a tiny French Mastiff lookalike 
4 years old
Needs work with other dogs, just no ability to read social cues, very workable she's come SO far in the past year 
NO cats
No young kids. Despite being great with kids in past fosters (but when overwhelmed it was the children in her home that she directed at, so we are now saying no kids)
Loves to cuddle
Crate trained (most of the time) and working on commands
House trained
Fully vetted
45lbs

I ran across this horrible intake photo of a sweet little red bully mix where you can't even tell if it's a tongue or a growth on her face and knew she wasn't likely to make it out. She was emaciated and had sores all over her legs and feet, she was drooling and obviously scared out of her mind. Do to her emaciated state she was immediately out in the rescue only building and thus very few people saw her. Then I watched 2 videos of her and her face kept me up at night. She was desperate and scared, and you could tell she's had a horrible life with very little human kindness! I couldn't stop thinking about her, checking her posts to see if they had the update we were all hoping for. 

As the California shelter continued to fill and there were no updates and she was going to die I reached out to some people to see if we could help in any way. I needed to see that she got her miracle, her 2nd chance, because in rescue that's what we do.

We got her pulled and she had horrible kennel cough and a URI. It was also discovered that her unique smile is likely because she suffers a birth defect that results in her not growing all her teeth, which gives her the most adorable smile ever! She stayed at the vet for a while where they determined she was dog reactive. Unfortunately because she went from one stressful kennel environment to another that's not an assessment that we can trust. She had a foster who was finally able to pick her up from the vet after a couple weeks. She kept her for a few weeks. When Scarlett arrived she was still super skinny.

Scarlett's life had been horrible, during her first 3 years on this planet she had seen little to no human kindness and yet, her favorite activity is cuddling with her humans and giving out lots of love! She's got the sweetest personality which makes the idea that she likely lived in a small area full of her own feces(sores on her feat and lack of care regarding sleeping in her own mess ), hit (scars), neglected (horrible condition she was in), starved (emaciated state) and ignored before basically being left to fend for herself on the mean streets of Los Angeles is epically heartbreaking! 

Even after a year Scarlett is a work in progress and need a PATIENT and epically understanding home. She hasn't been properly socialized with other dogs and thus she doesn't understand the concept of person space and she cannot read social cues, at all. Due to this we are looking for a home for her without other dogs. We believe with work and time in the future she may be just fine with other dogs, she has made great headway in the past year, but right now that's just not something we are willing to risk. After everything she's been through she really deserves to be insanely adored!

If you're willing to open up your home and heart to this adorable little flower please contact us ASAP! We are so excited to play such an epic role in her journey to find her FURever home and we cannot wait to meet her special humans wherever they are and watch her blossom in her own home! 

 $200.00 Adoption Fee 
(Which is considered a non refundable donation and being we are a 501c3 organization it is tax deductible. The fee itself is not negotiable, our vets don't negotiate and thus neither do we.) 

WE DO NOT HAVE A FACILITY ALL OUR DOGS ARE LOCATED IN FOSTER HOMES. This means there is no place for you to go in person to view our dogs. We ask that an application be filled out and we will go from there!

To Contact Us

Message us through our website http://www.highplainspaw.org

Message the Facebook Page at https://www.facebook.com/HighPlainsPAW

Fill out our Adoption Application at https://www.highplainspaw.org/adoption-application

Fill out our Foster Application at https://www.highplainspaw.org/foster-application

Email us at highplainspaw@gmail.com

Call our voicemail at (402)957-1578

animal.description:
Brisket is a 1.5 year old chocolate lab mix who was found wandering around an oil patch in rural Texas. We looked and looked for his owner but it seems they did not want to be found. All the better for Brisket because now he gets to find a new home who will take good care of him and make certain he never gets lost or abandoned. At 50-55 lbs, Brisket is a medium size boy who is perfect for those hikes, games of fetch and of course, snuggles on the couch! He has been a little growly toward some male dogs who get in his face so he has asked to be placed in a home with only female dogs or as an only child. Before he came to Colorado his Texas foster family said he slept quietly and contently in his crate and would walk right in - no fuss! This smart boy learned the routin quickly and only had 2 accidents in the house so he is pretty much house trained once he knows the routine. Kids adore him and Brisket returnes the sentiments. He was great with her kids and also didn't seem to mind the barn cats but that doesn't necessarily mean he will be great with every house cat. 

If you are interested in meeting Bart please complete an application at https://www.circle2rescue.com/dog-adoption-application/ The adoption fee of $350 includes spay/neuter, vaccinations, microchip and dewormer.

Please note, Circle 2 Rescue cannot guarantee the breed, composition or ages of our dogs as we usually have limited history prior to them entering the rescue. We make every effort to ensure the dogs are healthy.

animal.description:
0121061

I need a single family home with a fenced in yard since I require lots of physical and mental stimulation! 

My name is CHANEL I m approximately a 2 months or 10 weeks old female Boxer mix. Pictures just dont do me justice because I am much cuter in person; my medium black silky coat has a touch of white on my paws and stomach and when the sun shines on my coat there's a slight brown highlight and my foster mom loves my curly tail. I am a little more rambunctious than my brother Louie and Ill come running with pure excitement when I hear the word SIT because I know that I can earn lots of treats while learning my basic commands. Im also learning how to be gentle while taking my treats and sometimes I just get a little too excited but I AM NOT food aggressive. My foster mom uses training techniques from the TV show Its me or the dog which is positive reinforcement. Im still working on my potty training and I have very few accidents at night in my kennel. While my foster family is away, theyll provide me with plenty of chew toys with treats inside, although I like them I sometimes prefer to play with the other pups and my mom. Im a social girl but I can be reserved at times especially when my foster boy runs around, thats when Ill retreat to my kennel unless I feel like playing and chasing him with my mom. I love playing with other dogs but I havent been around cats yet and I love to cuddle with my humans. Im not huge on barking but will at times when Im engrossed in playing , other than that I pay no attention to the doorbell and it doesnt bother me when we have visitors. Overall I am super cute, a quick learner and ready to find my forever home.

0121062

I need a single family home with a fenced in yard since I require lots of physical and mental stimulation!

My name is GUCCI Im approximately 2 year old female Boxer mix with short white and black hair; my foster mom isnt sure what I a mixed with but thinks it might be a Basenji because of my curly tail and other features and I recently had two puppies Chanel and Louie that are now ready for adoption. When my foster family first brought me home I was overly rambunctious but with stimulation and lots of walks, Ive settled down quite a bit. Im really good with other dogs and I love to go on walks. I sometimes pull but for the most part I am good on a leash, however if you stand in one place too long I will try and take the leash from your hand, so lets keep walking lol. I can get cold easily so I wouldnt mind wearing a coat during walks. I havent been around cats yet but I love my little 4 year old human! We play catch, hide and seek, tug a war and lots of other games together; for the most part I do well but occasionally I will get so excited that I will bulldoze right through him especially if its a BALL. My little foster boy can also get overly excited and play rough or fall on me and I just keep playing with him. My foster mom loves to watch us play tug a war because I keep encouraging my little man to take the rope from my mouth, I like to initiate play and help him out if he loses his grip. If I could talk, I would tell you that my favorite human is the little boy because we play a lot together. My foster mom has been working on training me but I can be stubborn and I am motivated by treats. I do know sit, lay down and I have selected hearing when it comes to come. I dont know the command for dance but I love to free stand on my hind legs. Initially I would resource guard my food and water but with training and time, I no longer guard my food or water. My foster mother uses training techniques from the TV show Its me or the dog which encourages positive reinforcement. I am kennel trained as well as potty trained but Id love to sleep by your side or one the floor if youll let me. Ill do well in an active home where I can get a lot of attention and with someone who loves to play ball with me. I enjoy chewing on toys with treats but they need to be durable or they simply wont last. If you love BALLS as much as I do then well be perfect for each other!

My name is LOUIE Im approximately a 2 month or 10 week old male Boxer mix. Im a social boy but I can be reserved at times especially when my foster boy runs around, thats when Ill retreat to my kennel unless I feel like playing and chasing him with my mom. I love playing with other dogs but I havent been around cats yet and I love to cuddle with my humans. Im not huge on barking but will at times when Im engrossed in playing , other than that I pay no attention to the doorbell and it doesnt bother me when we have visitors. Overall I am super cute, a quick learner and ready to find my forever home.

animal.description:
Gracelynn is a playful pup looking for an adventure buddy. As a young girl, she's eager to learn the ropes of being a spoiled house dog. 

**This dog is heartworm positive and will be treated by the rescue and will be available for foster to adopt for a local family in or near Charleston, SC that is comfortable with the restriction requirements for the duration of treatment.

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please fill out an application. We do allow out of state adoptions and any transport costs are at the expense of the adopter. If you have further questions about this dog, please email us at ccradopt@gmail.com and someone will be in touch as soon as possible. Please note we are unable to hold dogs for adopters as this ties up valuable foster homes.

Please understand that we are an all volunteer group and we have jobs outside of this organization. We do our best to provide quick responses but occasionally they are a little slower. If you do not receive a response in 48 hours, please resend to make sure it's received.
